White House Press Secretary Robert Gibbs gave a briefing where he discussed the President's schedule for the week. He mentioned that the President will visit the National Counterterrorism Center and deliver remarks, as well as brief bipartisan leaders of Congress on the Afghanistan review. The President will also meet with his national security team and host a discussion on math and science education. Other topics discussed during the briefing include the recent militant attack in Afghanistan, the healthcare reform bill, job creation measures, and General McChrystal's public statements on Afghanistan.